Step 1: How your application is designed

You have two ways to access the Connections Service.

Method 1: Through API Gateway (Production)
Browser/Postman
      │
      ▼
API Gateway (8080)
      │
Authentication Filter
      │
Extracts UserId from JWT
      │
Adds Header
X-User-Id : 101
      │
      ▼
Connections Service (9030)
      │
RequestInterceptor
      │
Reads X-User-Id
      │
Controller

Everything works because the API Gateway adds the required header.

Method 2: Directly accessing the service
Browser
      │
      ▼
Connections Service (9030)

Here,

API Gateway is completely skipped.

So nobody adds

X-User-Id
Step 2: What happens when you open Swagger?

You typed

http://localhost:9030/connections/swagger-ui/index.html

The request flow becomes

Browser
    │
    ▼
Connections Service

Notice

API Gateway

is not in the flow.

Therefore

