This separation of responsibilities is the standard approach in Spring applications:

WebMvcConfigurer decides which requests should pass through the interceptor.
RequestInterceptor performs authentication/authorization logic only for the requests it receives.

That makes the configuration cleaner, easier to maintain, and avoids mixing URL-routing decisions with authentication logic.